  "text": "Minimal detectable change (MDC) is the lowest estimate of change of an outcome measure beyond random measurement error [CITATION_1] . MDC 90 (MDC at the 90% confidence margin) was calculated for the NPRS-NP using the formula, MDC 90 = z x √2 x SEM, where SEM is the standard error of measurement and z = 1.64 (z score for estimating a 90% confidence interval). We used square root of 2, because a total of two measurements were done for test-retest stability. Finally, we calculated SEM manually by using the formula, SEM = SD (1 -r) 1/2 [CITATION_2] where SD is the standard deviation for the mean change of NPRS-NP score from baseline to final measurement, and r = reliability coefficient i.e. Intra-class Correlation Coefficient (ICC) of the stable group. We hypothesized that the MDC 90 value would lie between 0.5 and 2.5 [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
